Patch Set 1:

@Fei

Thank you for your advise.

There are question about test_db.py.

In test_db.py, FakeDB is used as Database.
 -https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/test_db.py#L103
 -https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/test_db.py#L25

And, although FakeDB uses simple db module, I seem that "changes-since"
function isn't implemented in simple db module.
 -https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/utils.py#L21
 -https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/tests/unit/utils.py#L90
 -https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/db/simple/api.py#L350
 -https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/db/simple/api.py#L206

It would be great if you could answer my question.
 -Is my understanding is correct?
 -Is it bug?

If my understanding correct, we will reconsider the place of test case.

background)
  Although I add test source as below in TestImageRepo class, it doesn't work.
As a result of looking at source, I can't find "changes-since" keyword in simple DB.

 test source:
    def test_list_with_filters_changes_since(self):
        dt = timeutils.utcnow() + datetime.timedelta(4)
        changes_since_ts = datetime.datetime(dt.year, dt.month,
                                             dt.day, dt.hour,
                                             dt.minute, dt.second)
        changes_since = changes_since_ts.strftime('%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
        image = _db_fixture(UUID5, owner=TENANT5, name='5', size=4098,
                            is_public=True, checksum=CHECKSUM,
                            updated_at=changes_since_ts,
                            created_at=changes_since_ts)
        self.db.image_create(None, image)
        filters = {'changes-since': changes_since}
        images = self.image_repo.list()

        image_ids = set([i.image_id for i in images])
        self.assertEqual(set([UUID1, UUID2, UUID3, UUID5]), image_ids)

        images = self.image_repo.list(filters=filters)
        image_ids = list([i.image_id for i in images])
        self.assertEqual(1, len(image_ids))
        self.assertEqual([UUID5], image_ids)
        self.db.image_destroy(None, UUID5)

thank
